{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862881112,"sessionID":"ses_28653205affeCYrhnPGU1oCRmh","part":{"id":"prt_d79ad15fe001SF44XsIiUdkdjQ","messageID":"msg_d79acfa61001ma1bCukfMSm5yb","sessionID":"ses_28653205affeCYrhnPGU1oCRmh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f029be40fe73439aa3884418","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n18:   - Define package-level imports: `crypto/rsa`, `crypto/x509`, `encoding/pem`, `encoding/base64`\n19: \n20: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `LoadPublicKey(pemData []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n21:   - Parse PEM block from data\n22:   - Delegate to ParsePEM for key extraction\n23:   - Return error if PEM parsing fails\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Implement `LoadPublicKeyFromBase64(base64PEM string) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n26:   - Decode base64 string to bytes\n27:   - Call LoadPublicKey with decoded bytes\n28:   - Handle base64 decoding errors\n29: \n30: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `ParsePEM(pemBlock *pem.Block) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n31:   - Handle PKIX format (x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey)\n32:   - Handle PKCS#1 format (x509.ParsePKCS1PublicKey)\n33:   - Return error for unsupported formats\n34: \n35: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `GenerateKeyPair(bits int) (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n36:   - Generate RSA key pair using rsa.GenerateKey\n37:   - Return private and public keys\n38:   - Use crypto/rand for secure random generation\n39: \n40: ### Phase 2: JWT Claims & Validation (`jwt.go`)\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `Claims` struct in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n43:   - Fields: `Sub` (string), `Iss` (string), `Aud` (string), `Exp` (int64), `Iat` (int64), `SandboxID` (string), `Namespace` (string)\n44:   - JSON tags for all fields\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Validate(c *Claims, now time.Time, clockSkew time.Duration) error` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n47:   - Check expiration (exp + clockSkew < now → expired)\n48:   - Check not before (iat - clockSkew > now → not yet valid)\n49:   - Validate required claims (sub, iss, aud, exp, iat present)\n50:   - Return appropriate error for each validation failure\n51: \n52: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `ParseAndValidate(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, clockSkew time.Duration) (*Claims, error)` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n53:   - Split token into header.payload.signature\n54:   - Verify signature using VerifySignature\n55:   - Parse payload JSON into Claims\n56:   - Validate claims using Validate\n57:   - Return parsed claims or error\n58: \n59: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `VerifySignature(tokenString string, publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) error` in `pkg/picod/jwt.go`\n60:   - Decode header and payload (base64url)\n61:   - Decode signature (base64url)\n62:   - Construct signing input: `header.payload`\n63:   - Verify RSA-PKCS1v15 signature (SHA256)\n64:   - Return error if signature invalid\n65: \n66: ### Phase 3: Authentication Errors (`errors.go`)\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `AuthErrorType` type and constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n69:   - Type: `AuthErrorType` (string alias)\n70:   - Constants: `AuthErrorMissingToken`, `AuthErrorInvalidToken`, `AuthErrorExpiredToken`, `AuthErrorInvalidSig`, `AuthErrorInvalidClaims`, `AuthErrorInternal`\n71: \n72: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `AuthError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n73:   - Fields: `Type` (AuthErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n74:   - Methods: `Error() string`, `Unwrap() error`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `HTTPStatus(e *AuthError) int` in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n77:   - Map error types to HTTP status codes:\n78:     - MissingToken, InvalidToken, InvalidSig, InvalidClaims → 401\n79:     - ExpiredToken → 401\n80:     - Internal → 500\n81: \n82: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `NewAuthError(authType AuthErrorType, message string, underlying error) *AuthError` in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n83:   - Constructor for AuthError\n84:   - Format message with context\n85: \n86: ### Phase 4: HTTP Middleware (`middleware.go`)\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Define `JWTMiddleware` struct in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n89:   - Fields: `publicKey` (*rsa.PublicKey), `skipPaths` (map[string]bool), `clockSkew` (time.Duration), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n90: \n91: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewJWTMiddleware(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, clockSkew time.Duration, skipPaths ...string) *JWTMiddleware` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n92:   - Initialize skipPaths map\n93:   - Set default clockSkew (30 seconds if 0)\n94:   - Create structured logger\n95: \n96: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Middleware(m *JWTMiddleware, next http.Handler) http.Handler` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n97:   - Wrap handler with authentication logic\n98:   - Extract path from request\n99:   - Check if path should skip auth\n100:   - Extract token from Authorization header\n101:   - Validate token\n102:   - Call next handler on success, return error on failure\n103: \n104: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `extractToken(m *JWTMiddleware, r *http.Request) (string, error)` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n105:   - Get Authorization header\n106:   - Validate \"Bearer \" prefix\n107:   - Extract token string\n108:   - Return error if missing or malformed\n109: \n110: - [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `shouldSkip(m *JWTMiddleware, path string) bool` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n111:   - Check if path exists in skipPaths map\n112:   - Support exact path matching\n113: \n114: ### Phase 5: HTTP Response Helpers (`middleware.go`)\n115: \n116: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `WriteJSON(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n117:   - Set Content-Type header\n118:   - Set status code\n119:   - Encode data as JSON\n120:   - Handle encoding errors\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `WriteAuthError(w http.ResponseWriter, err *AuthError)` in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n123:   - Get HTTP status from error\n124:   - Write JSON error response\n125:   - Include error type and message\n126: \n127: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Define `HealthResponse` struct in `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n128:   - Fields: `Status` (string), `Timestamp` (time.Time), `SandboxID` (string)\n129:   - JSON tags for all fields\n130: \n131: ### Phase 6: Configuration (`config.go`)\n132: \n133: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Add auth fields to `Config` struct in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n134:   - Fields: `AuthMode` (string), `PublicKeyPEM` (string), `SkipPaths` ([]string), `ClockSkew` (time.Duration)\n135: \n136: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Update `LoadConfig()` in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n137:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_MODE` (default: \"none\")\n138:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` (required if AuthMode=picod)\n139:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_SKIP_PATHS` (default: \"/health\", comma-separated)\n140:   - Load `PICOD_AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW` (default: 30s)\n141: \n142: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Add command-line flag parsing helpers in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n143:   - `ParseAuthFlags()` function\n144:   - Flags: `-auth`, `-public-key`, `-skip-paths`, `-clock-skew`\n145:   - Merge flags with environment variables (flags take precedence)\n146: \n147: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `Validate(c *Config) error` for auth config in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n148:   - If AuthMode=\"picod\", require PublicKeyPEM\n149:   - Validate clockSkew is non-negative\n150:   - Parse and validate skip paths\n151: \n152: ### Phase 7: PicoD Integration (`picod.go`)\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Add `authMode` and `publicKey` fields to `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n155:   - Fields: `authMode` (string), `publicKey` (*rsa.PublicKey)\n156: \n157: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Add `WithAuthMode(mode string) Option` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n158:   - Functional option to set auth mode\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Add `WithPublicKey(pem string) Option` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n161:   - Functional option to set public key\n162:   - Load key from PEM\n163: \n164: - [ ] **TASK-063**: Implement `SetupHTTPServer(picod *PicoD, config *Config) (*http.Server, error)` in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n165:   - Create ServeMux\n166:   - Register handlers\n167:   - Apply JWT middleware if AuthMode=picod\n168:   - Configure ReadHeaderTimeout (10s)\n169: \n170: ### Phase 8: Unit Tests\n171: \n172: #### Crypto Tests\n173: \n174: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestLoadPublicKey_Success` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n175:   - Load valid PKIX PEM key\n176:   - Verify key returned without error\n177: \n178: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestLoadPublicKeyFromBase64` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n179:   - Load base64-encoded PEM key\n180:   - Verify decoded key matches direct load\n181: \n182: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestLoadPublicKey_InvalidPEM` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n183:   - Load invalid PEM data\n184:   - Verify error returned\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestGenerateKeyPair` in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n187:   - Generate key pair (2048 bits)\n188:   - Verify private and public keys not nil\n189: \n190: #### JWT Tests\n191: \n192: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Success` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n193:   - Valid claims with future exp\n194:   - Verify no error\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Expired` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n197:   - Claims with past exp\n198:   - Verify error returned\n199: \n200: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_Future` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n201:   - Claims with future iat\n202:   - Verify error returned\n203: \n204: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Create `TestClaims_Validate_MissingClaims` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n205:   - Claims missing required fields\n206:   - Verify error returned\n207: \n208: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Create `TestParseAndValidate_Success` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n209:   - Generate valid token with test key\n210:   - Parse and validate\n211:   - Verify claims extracted correctly\n212: \n213: - [ ] **TEST-015**: Create `TestParseAndValidate_InvalidSignature` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n214:   - Tamper with token signature\n215:   - Verify signature verification fails\n216: \n217: - [ ] **TEST-016**: Create `TestVerifySignature_RS256` in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n218:   - Verify RS256 signature algorithm\n219:   - Test with known token\n220: \n221: #### Error Tests\n222: \n223: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `TestAuthError_ErrorTypes` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n224:   - Verify all error types defined\n225:   - Verify Error() method works\n226: \n227: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `TestAuthError_HTTPStatus` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n228:   - Each error type maps to correct HTTP status\n229:   - 401 for auth errors, 500 for internal\n230: \n231: #### Middleware Tests\n232: \n233: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_ValidToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n234:   - Request with valid JWT token\n235:   - Verify next handler called\n236:   - Verify request passes through\n237: \n238: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_MissingToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n239:   - Request without Authorization header\n240:   - Verify 401 returned\n241:   - Verify next handler not called\n242: \n243: - [ ] **TEST-032**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n244:   - Request with malformed token\n245:   - Verify 401 returned\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-033**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_ExpiredToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n248:   - Request with expired token\n249:   - Verify 401 returned\n250: \n251: - [ ] **TEST-034**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_SkipPath` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n252:   - Request to /health (skipped path)\n253:   - Verify auth not required\n254:   - Verify next handler called\n255: \n256: - [ ] **TEST-035**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidAuthHeader` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n257:   - Request with non-Bearer auth scheme\n258:   - Verify 401 returned\n259: \n260: - [ ] **TEST-036**: Create `TestExtractToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n261:   - Valid Bearer header → token extracted\n262:   - Missing header → error\n263:   - Malformed header → error\n264: \n265: #### Config Tests\n266: \n267: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `TestLoadConfig_AuthConfig` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n268:   - Load auth config from environment\n269:   - Verify defaults applied\n270: \n271: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Create `TestConfig_Validate_AuthMode` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n272:   - AuthMode=picod without key → error\n273:   - AuthMode=picod with key → valid\n274:   - AuthMode=none → valid\n275: \n276: ### Phase 9: Integration Tests\n277: \n278: - [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_FullFlow` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n279:   - Start real HTTP server with JWT middleware\n280:   - Make request with valid token\n281:   - Verify 200 OK\n282:   - Make request without token\n283:   - Verify 401 Unauthorized\n284: \n285: - [ ] **TEST-051**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_MultipleRequests` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n286:   - Concurrent requests with valid tokens\n287:   - Verify all succeed\n288:   - Verify no race conditions (run with -race)\n289: \n290: - [ ] **TEST-052**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_HealthEndpoint` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n291:   - Health endpoint without token → 200 OK\n292:   - Protected endpoint without token → 401\n293:   - Verify skip paths work in real server\n294: \n295: - [ ] **TEST-053**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_TokenTampering` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n296:   - Modify valid token payload\n297:   - Verify signature check fails\n298:   - Verify 401 returned\n299: \n300: - [ ] **TEST-054**: Create `TestSetupHTTPServer_Integration` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n301:   - Full server setup with auth enabled\n302:   - Verify middleware applied\n303:   - Verify server responds correctly\n304: \n305: ### Phase 10: Documentation\n306: \n307: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types in `crypto.go`, `jwt.go`, `errors.go`, `middleware.go`\n308:   - Include parameter descriptions\n309:   - Include return value descriptions\n310:   - Include error conditions\n311: \n312: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add usage examples in doc comments\n313:   - Example: creating JWT middleware\n314:   - Example: loading public key\n315:   - Example: validating token\n316: \n317: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update `pkg/picod/README.md`\n318:   - Document JWT authentication\n319:   - Include configuration options\n320:   - Include token format requirements\n321:   - Include error handling guide\n322: \n323: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add security documentation\n324:   - RSA key management best practices\n325:   - Token lifetime recommendations\n326:   - Clock skew considerations\n327:   - Key rotation strategy\n328: \n329: ## Acceptance Criteria\n330: \n331: - [ ] JWT middleware correctly validates tokens with RSA signatures\n332: - [ ] Invalid/missing tokens return 401 Unauthorized\n333: - [ ] Expired tokens are rejected\n334: - [ ] Signature verification works with RSA public key (PKIX and PKCS#1 formats)\n335: - [ ] Configurable skip paths work correctly\n336: - [ ] Health endpoint can be protected or public\n337: - [ ] Claims are correctly parsed and validated (exp, iat, sub, iss, aud)\n338: - [ ] Clock skew tolerance is configurable\n339: - [ ] Error types map to appropriate HTTP status codes\n340: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n341: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n342: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n343: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n344: - [ ] Compatible with standard JWT libraries (PyJWT, node-jose, etc.)\n345: - [ ] RS256 (RSA-PKCS1v15 with SHA256) signature algorithm implemented\n346: \n347: ## Dependencies\n348: \n349: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n350: |------------|--------|-------|\n351: | `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA signature verification |\n352: | `crypto/x509` | Standard | X.509 key parsing |\n353: | `crypto/rand` | Standard | Key generation |\n354: | `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM decoding |\n355: | `encoding/base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding |\n356: | `encoding/json` | Standard | JSON claims parsing |\n357: | `net/http` | Standard | HTTP middleware |\n358: | `strings` | Standard | String manipulation |\n359: | `time` | Standard | Token time validation |\n360: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n361: | AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n362: | AR-016 (PicoD File Management API) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n363: \n364: ## Implementation Order\n365: \n366: ```\n367: TASK-001 → TASK-005 (Crypto utilities)\n368:     ↓\n369: TASK-010 → TASK-013 (JWT claims & validation)\n370:     ↓\n371: TASK-020 → TASK-023 (Auth errors)\n372:     ↓\n373: TASK-030 → TASK-034 (HTTP middleware)\n374:     ↓\n375: TASK-040 → TASK-042 (Response helpers)\n376:     ↓\n377: TASK-050 → TASK-053 (Configuration)\n378:     ↓\n379: TASK-060 → TASK-063 (PicoD integration)\n380:     ↓\n381: TEST-001 → TEST-041 (Unit tests)\n382:     ↓\n383: TEST-050 → TEST-054 (Integration tests)\n384:     ↓\n385: DOC-001 → DOC-004 (Documentation)\n386: ```\n387: \n388: ## Test Infrastructure\n389: \n390: - [ ] **TEST-060**: Create `generateTestToken(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, claims *Claims) (string, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n391:   - Create JWT header (RS256)\n392:   - Encode claims as JSON\n393:   - Sign with private key\n394:   - Return complete token\n395: \n396: - [ ] **TEST-061**: Create `testClaims() *Claims` helper in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n397:   - Return standard test claims with valid timestamps\n398: \n399: - [ ] **TEST-062**: Create `generateTestKeyPair() (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n400:   - Generate RSA key pair for tests\n401:   - Use smaller key size (1024 bits) for speed\n402: \n403: - [ ] **TEST-063**: Create `newTestServer(handler http.Handler) (*httptest.Server, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n404:   - Create test HTTP server\n405:   - Return server and cleanup function\n406: \n407: ## Coverage Verification\n408: \n409: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n410:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/picod/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n411:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n412:   - Verify crypto.go, jwt.go, errors.go, middleware.go all covered\n413:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n414: \n415: ## Security Considerations\n416: \n417: - [ ] **SEC-001**: Verify RSA signature uses SHA256 (RS256)\n418: - [ ] **SEC-002**: Verify clock skew prevents replay attacks\n419: - [ ] **SEC-003**: Verify token parsing rejects malformed input\n420: - [ ] **SEC-004**: Verify key loading rejects invalid formats\n421: - [ ] **SEC-005**: Verify error messages don't leak sensitive info\n\n(End of file - total 421 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n  - Define package-level imports: `crypto/rsa`, `crypto/x509`, `encoding/pem`, `encoding/base64`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `LoadPublicKey(pemData []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775862881081,"end":1775862881111}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862881114,"sessionID":"ses_28653205affeCYrhnPGU1oCRmh","part":{"id":"prt_d79ad10fe001Jdxalb1wkT8CC5","messageID":"msg_d79acfa61001ma1bCukfMSm5yb","sessionID":"ses_28653205affeCYrhnPGU1oCRmh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a396bf52e33748d5a15870f8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the idle cleanup controller implementation for `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: IdleCleanupController interface\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `IdleCleanupController` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` with methods `Start(ctx context.Context) error`, `Stop()`, and `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)`. `CleanupResult` SHALL include `AgentRuntimesCleaned int`, `CodeInterpretersCleaned int`, and `Errors []CleanupError`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Start idle cleanup controller\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** a configured `IdleCleanupController` with `Enabled = true`\n16: - **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called during agentd initialization\n17: - **THEN** the controller SHALL start periodic cleanup cycles at `CleanupInterval` and watch resource events\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Stop controller gracefully\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a running `IdleCleanupController`\n22: - **WHEN** `Stop()` is called during shutdown\n23: - **THEN** the controller SHALL stop watching resources and complete in-flight cleanup operations\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Trigger immediate cleanup\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** idle resources exist exceeding configured timeouts\n28: - **WHEN** `CleanupNow(ctx)` is called manually\n29: - **THEN** an immediate cleanup cycle SHALL run and return `CleanupResult` with counts of cleaned resources\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Controller disabled\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.Enabled = false`\n34: - **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called\n35: - **THEN** the controller SHALL log \"Idle cleanup controller is disabled\" and return nil without starting watches or cleanup\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: CleanupResult with errors\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** cleanup encounters errors during deletion\n40: - **WHEN** `CleanupNow(ctx)` completes\n41: - **THEN** `CleanupResult.Errors` SHALL contain `CleanupError` entries for each failed resource\n42: \n43: ### Requirement: IdleTracker interface\n44: \n45: The system SHALL define `IdleTracker` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` with methods `UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)`, `GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)`, `IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool`, `Remove(kind, namespace, name string)`, and `ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey`. `ResourceKey` SHALL include `Kind`, `Namespace`, and `Name` fields.\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Update last activity timestamp\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** an `IdleTracker` instance\n50: - **WHEN** `UpdateLastActivity(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", now)` is called\n51: - **THEN** the last activity for the resource SHALL be stored and retrievable via `GetLastActivity`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Check if resource is idle\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a resource with last activity 35 minutes ago\n56: - **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n57: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `true`\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Resource not yet idle\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** a resource with last activity 10 minutes ago\n62: - **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n63: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `false`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: No activity recorded\n66: \n67: - **GIVEN** a resource never had activity recorded via `UpdateLastActivity`\n68: - **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n69: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `true` (treat as idle)\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: List all idle resources\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** multiple resources with varying last activity times\n74: - **WHEN** `ListIdleResources(30*time.Minute)` is called\n75: - **THEN** only resources idle for >= 30 minutes SHALL be returned\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Remove resource from tracking\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** a tracked resource in `IdleTracker`\n80: - **WHEN** `Remove(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** the resource SHALL no longer appear in `ListIdleResources` or `GetLastActivity`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Thread-safe activity updates\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** concurrent calls to `UpdateLastActivity` from multiple goroutines\n86: - **WHEN** activity updates occur simultaneously\n87: - **THEN** all updates SHALL be applied correctly without data races\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: CleanupConfig structure\n90: \n91: The system SHALL define `CleanupConfig` in `pkg/agentd/config.go` with fields `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CleanupInterval time.Duration`, `MaxConcurrentCleanups int`, `Enabled bool`, `DryRun bool`, `NamespaceAllowList []string`, and `NamespaceDenyList []string`. `DefaultCleanupConfig()` SHALL return config with AgentRuntime timeout 30m, CodeInterpreter timeout 15m, interval 5m, max concurrent 10, enabled true.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Default configuration values\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `DefaultCleanupConfig()` is called\n96: - **WHEN** the configuration is inspected\n97: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout` SHALL be `30 * time.Minute`\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Default CodeInterpreter timeout\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** `DefaultCleanupConfig()` is called\n102: - **WHEN** the configuration is inspected\n103: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Dry-run mode enabled\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.DryRun = true`\n108: - **WHEN** cleanup runs\n109: - **THEN** resources SHALL be logged but not deleted from the API server\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Namespace allow list filtering\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** `NamespaceAllowList = []string{\"default\", \"agents\"}`\n114: - **WHEN** cleanup evaluates a resource in namespace `\"other\"`\n115: - **THEN** the resource SHALL NOT be cleaned (namespace not allowed)\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Namespace deny list filtering\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** `NamespaceDenyList = []string{\"kube-system\", \"monitoring\"}`\n120: - **WHEN** cleanup evaluates a resource in namespace `\"kube-system\"`\n121: - **THEN** the resource SHALL NOT be cleaned (namespace denied)\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Max concurrent cleanups limit\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** `MaxConcurrentCleanups = 5` and 20 idle resources\n126: - **WHEN** cleanup cycle runs\n127: - **THEN** at most 5 deletion operations SHALL execute concurrently\n128: \n129: ### Requirement: Watch AgentRuntime resources\n130: \n131: The system SHALL implement `watchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context)` method that uses `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(metav1.NamespaceAll).Watch()` to monitor resource events. On `Added` or `Modified` events, update idle tracker with `Status.LastActivityTime` or `CreationTimestamp`. On `Deleted` events, remove from tracker.\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Watch receives Added event\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** a new AgentRuntime `\"ar-1\"` is created in namespace `\"default\"`\n136: - **WHEN** the watch receives the `Added` event\n137: - **THEN** `IdleTracker.UpdateLastActivity` SHALL be called with the resource's `CreationTimestamp`\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Watch receives Modified event with last activity\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with `Status.LastActivityTime` updated\n142: - **WHEN** the watch receives the `Modified` event\n143: - **THEN** `IdleTracker.UpdateLastActivity` SHALL be called with `LastActivityTime`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Watch receives Deleted event\n146: \n147: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime is deleted from the cluster\n148: - **WHEN** the watch receives the `Deleted` event\n149: - **THEN** the resource SHALL be removed from `IdleTracker`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Watch reconnection on failure\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** the watch connection fails\n154: - **WHEN** the watch channel closes\n155: - **THEN** the controller SHALL re-establish the watch with exponential backoff\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Watch context cancellation\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** the context is cancelled during shutdown\n160: - **WHEN** `ctx.Done()` is signaled\n161: - **THEN** the watch SHALL stop and call `watcher.Stop()`\n162: \n163: ### Requirement: Cleanup AgentRuntime resources\n164: \n165: The system SHALL implement `cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error` that calls `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete()` with `GracePeriodSeconds: 30` and `PropagationPolicy: Foreground`. Metrics SHALL be recorded for duration and success/failure.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Delete idle AgentRuntime\n168: \n169: - **GIVEN** an idle AgentRuntime `\"ar-1\"` in namespace `\"default\"`\n170: - **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called for this resource\n171: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be deleted from the API server\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Delete with grace period\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** `cleanupResource` is called for an AgentRuntime\n176: - **WHEN** the delete operation executes\n177: - **THEN** `GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30 seconds\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Foreground propagation policy\n180: \n181: - **GIVEN** `cleanupResource` deletes an AgentRuntime\n182: - **WHEN** the delete options are set\n183: - **THEN** `PropagationPolicy` SHALL be `DeletePropagationForeground`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Cleanup non-existent resource\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime was already deleted by another process\n188: - **WHEN** `cleanupResource` attempts deletion\n189: - **THEN** a `NotFound` error SHALL be handled gracefully (logged, not retried)\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Dry-run skips deletion\n192: \n193: - **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.DryRun = true`\n194: - **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called\n195: - **THEN** the method SHALL log the action but NOT call the delete API\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: Cleanup CodeInterpreter resources\n198: \n199: The system SHALL implement cleanup for CodeInterpreters using `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()` with the same grace period and propagation policy as AgentRuntimes.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Delete idle CodeInterpreter\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** an idle CodeInterpreter `\"ci-1\"` in namespace `\"default\"`\n204: - **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called for this resource\n205: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from the API server\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n208: \n209: - **GIVEN** `watchCodeInterpreters(ctx)` is running\n210: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created, modified, or deleted\n211: - **THEN** the `IdleTracker` SHALL be updated accordingly\n212: \n213: ### Requirement: CleanupMetrics\n214: \n215: The system SHALL define `CleanupMetrics` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` with Prometheus counters `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal`, `codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal`, `cleanupErrorsTotal`, histogram `cleanupDurationSeconds`, and gauge `idleResourcesDetected`. Methods SHALL include `RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)`, `SetIdleCount(kind string, count int)`, and `RecordError(kind string)`.\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Record successful cleanup\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime was successfully cleaned\n220: - **WHEN** `RecordCleanup(\"AgentRuntime\", 2*time.Second, nil)` is called\n221: - **THEN** `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal` counter SHALL increment and duration histogram updated\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Record cleanup error\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter cleanup failed\n226: - **WHEN** `RecordCleanup(\"CodeInterpreter\", 1*time.Second, err)` is called\n227: - **THEN** `cleanupErrorsTotal` counter SHALL increment with kind label\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Set idle resource count\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** 15 idle AgentRuntimes detected\n232: - **WHEN** `SetIdleCount(\"AgentRuntime\", 15)` is called\n233: - **THEN** `idleResourcesDetected` gauge SHALL be set to 15\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Metrics exposed via Prometheus\n236: \n237: - **GIVEN** the metrics registry is registered with Prometheus\n238: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint is scraped\n239: - **THEN** all cleanup metrics SHALL be visible with proper labels\n240: \n241: ### Requirement: Namespace filtering\n242: \n243: The system SHALL implement `isNamespaceAllowed(namespace string) bool` method that checks deny list first, then allow list. System namespaces `kube-system` and `kube-public` SHALL be in the default deny list.\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Deny list takes precedence\n246: \n247: - **GIVEN** namespace `\"monitoring\"` is in both allow and deny lists\n248: - **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"monitoring\")` is called\n249: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `false` (denied)\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Empty allow list allows all\n252: \n253: - **GIVEN** `NamespaceAllowList` is empty\n254: - **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"any-namespace\")` is called for a non-denied namespace\n255: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `true`\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Default system namespace denial\n258: \n259: - **GIVEN** default configuration\n260: - **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"kube-system\")` is called\n261: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `false`\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: Periodic cleanup cycle\n264: \n265: The system SHALL implement `runCleanup(ctx context.Context)` that runs at `CleanupInterval`, lists idle resources for both types, and cleans allowed namespaces concurrently respecting `MaxConcurrentCleanups`.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Periodic cleanup execution\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** `CleanupInterval = 5 * time.Minute`\n270: - **WHEN** the controller is running\n271: - **THEN** `runCleanup` SHALL be invoked every 5 minutes\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Cleanup both resource types\n274: \n275: - **GIVEN** idle AgentRuntimes and CodeInterpreters exist\n276: - **WHEN** `runCleanup` executes\n277: - **THEN** both resource types SHALL be processed in the same cycle\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Concurrent cleanup with limit\n280: \n281: - **GIVEN** 50 idle resources and `MaxConcurrentCleanups = 10`\n282: - **WHEN** cleanup runs\n283: - **THEN** cleanup operations SHALL execute in batches of at most 10 concurrent deletions\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Cleanup cycle logs summary\n286: \n287: - **GIVEN** cleanup cycle completes\n288: - **WHEN** all operations finish\n289: - **THEN** a log message SHALL indicate number of resources cleaned and any errors\n290: \n291: ### Requirement: Environment variable configuration\n292: \n293: The system SHALL support configuration via environment variables: `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN`, `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL`, `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST`.\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Load cleanup enabled from env\n296: \n297: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED=false` is set\n298: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n299: - **THEN** `CleanupConfig.Enabled` SHALL be `false`\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Load idle timeout from env\n302: \n303: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT=1h` is set\n304: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n305: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout` SHALL be `1 * time.Hour`\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: Load namespace allow list from env\n308: \n309: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST=\"default,agents\"` is set\n310: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n311: - **THEN** `NamespaceAllowList` SHALL be `[]string{\"default\", \"agents\"}`\n312: \n313: #### Scenario: Invalid duration falls back to default\n314: \n315: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=invalid` is set\n316: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n317: - **THEN** the default interval SHALL be used and a warning logged\n318: \n319: ### Requirement: CleanupError types\n320: \n321: The system SHALL define `CleanupError` struct with fields `Type CleanupErrorType`, `ResourceKind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`, `Message string`, and `Underlying error`. Error types SHALL include `CleanupErrorNotFound`, `CleanupErrorPermission`, `CleanupErrorTimeout`, `CleanupErrorConflict`, and `CleanupErrorUnknown`.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: NotFound error handling\n324: \n325: - **GIVEN** resource is already deleted when cleanup attempts\n326: - **WHEN** API returns NotFound error\n327: - **THEN** `CleanupError.Type` SHALL be `CleanupErrorNotFound` and error is ignored\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Permission denied error\n330: \n331: - **GIVEN** RBAC does not allow delete on resource\n332: - **WHEN** cleanup attempts deletion\n333: - **THEN** `CleanupError.Type` SHALL be `CleanupErrorPermission` and logged for review\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Error string formatting\n336: \n337: - **GIVEN** a `CleanupError` with kind=\"AgentRuntime\", namespace=\"default\", name=\"ar-1\"\n338: - **WHEN** `Error()` is called\n339: - **THEN** the string SHALL include resource identification and error message\n340: \n341: ### Requirement: Graceful shutdown\n342: \n343: The system SHALL implement graceful shutdown in `Stop()` that closes `stopCh`, waits for in-flight cleanups via `sync.WaitGroup`, and logs shutdown completion.\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Stop closes stop channel\n346: \n347: - **GIVEN** a running controller\n348: - **WHEN** `Stop()` is called\n349: - **THEN** `stopCh` SHALL be closed signaling goroutines to exit\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Wait for goroutines to finish\n352: \n353: - **GIVEN** cleanup goroutines are running\n354: - **WHEN** `Stop()` is called\n355: - **THEN** the method SHALL block until all goroutines complete via `wg.Wait()`\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Shutdown logging\n358: \n359: - **GIVEN** controller shutdown completes\n360: - **WHEN** all goroutines exit\n361: - **THEN** a log message SHALL indicate \"Idle cleanup controller stopped\"\n362: \n363: ### Requirement: Integration with client-go\n364: \n365: The system SHALL use generated client-go from `deployment/client-go.md` including `versioned.Interface` for typed client access, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` for resource operations, and `watch.Interface` for event streaming.\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Create typed client for AgentRuntimes\n368: \n369: - **GIVEN** a configured `versioned.Interface` client\n370: - **WHEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\")` is called\n371: - **THEN** a typed `AgentRuntimeInterface` SHALL be returned for CRUD operations\n372: \n373: #### Scenario: Watch with typed client\n374: \n375: - **GIVEN** a typed `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n376: - **WHEN** `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})` is called\n377: - **THEN** a `watch.Interface` SHALL stream `Added`, `Modified`, `Deleted` events\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: List idle resources with label selector\n380: \n381: - **GIVEN** resources with various labels\n382: - **WHEN** `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=test\"})` is called\n383: - **THEN** only matching resources SHALL be returned for idle evaluation\n384: \n385: ## Dependencies\n386: \n387: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n388: |------------|--------|-------|\n389: | `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Kubernetes client interfaces |\n390: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated | Typed client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n391: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Generated | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n392: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch` | External | Watch event streaming |\n393: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | External | Metadata, deletion options |\n394: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n395: | `prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | External | Metrics exposition |\n396: | `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | External | Concurrent cleanup with limits |\n397: \n398: ## Files to Create/Modify\n399: \n400: | File | Action | Description |\n401: |------|--------|-------------|\n402: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` | Create | IdleCleanupController interface and implementation |\n403: | `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` | Create | IdleTracker interface and implementation |\n404: | `pkg/agentd/config.go` | Create | CleanupConfig structure and loading |\n405: | `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` | Create | Prometheus metrics for cleanup |\n406: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for cleanup controller |\n407: | `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for idle detection |\n408: | `pkg/agentd/config_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for configuration |\n409: | `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for metrics |\n410: \n411: ## Testing Strategy\n412: \n413: 1. **Unit Tests**: Mock client-go interfaces, test idle detection logic, verify namespace filtering\n414: 2. **Integration Tests**: Use fake clientset from `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/`, test full cleanup flows\n415: 3. **Concurrent Tests**: Verify thread-safety of IdleTracker under concurrent access\n416: 4. **Error Injection Tests**: Use reactors on fake client to test error handling paths\n\n(End of file - total 416 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the idle cleanup controller implementation for `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: IdleCleanupController interface\n\nThe system SHALL define `IdleCleanupController` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` with methods `Start(ctx context.Context) error`, `Stop()`, and `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)`. `CleanupResult` SHALL include `AgentRuntimesCleaned int`, `CodeInterpretersCleaned int`, and `Errors []CleanupError`.\n\n#### Scenario: Start idle cleanup controller\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured `IdleCleanupController` with `Enabled = true`\n- **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called during agentd initialization\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL start periodic cleanup cycles at `CleanupInterval` and watch resource events\n\n#### Scenario: Stop controller gracefully\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775862881078,"end":1775862881113}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862881118,"sessionID":"ses_28653205affeCYrhnPGU1oCRmh","part":{"id":"prt_d79ad05d30010HYu2Y0ynfXR3T","messageID":"msg_d79acfa61001ma1bCukfMSm5yb","sessionID":"ses_28653205affeCYrhnPGU1oCRmh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7e21cbb7f4ac41aa8337d9a3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (AR-018)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement an idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller provides:\n12: \n13: 1. **Resource Reclamation**: Automatically clean up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters to free cluster resources\n14: 2. **Configurable Idle Detection**: Support per-resource-type idle timeout configuration\n15: 3. **Graceful Termination**: Properly finalize resources before deletion with status updates\n16: 4. **Observability**: Emit metrics and logs for cleanup operations\n17: 5. **Safe Operation**: Respect resource11s and avoid cleaning resources with active workloads\n18: \n19: This implementation builds upon the client-go infrastructure from `deployment/client-go.md` and integrates with the workload manager's reconciliation loop to ensure cleaned resources are properly handled.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` - Idle cleanup controller interface and implementation\n28: - `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` - Idle state tracking and timeout detection\n29: - `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` - Metrics for cleanup operations\n30: - `pkg/agentd/config.go` - Configuration for idle timeouts and cleanup behavior\n31: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` - Unit tests for cleanup logic\n32: - `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go` - Unit tests for idle detection\n33: - `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go` - Integration tests with fake clients\n34: \n35: ### Out of Scope\n36: \n37: - Manual termination APIs (covered by workload manager handlers)\n38: - Resource scaling policies (future AR)\n39: - Cross-namespace cleanup coordination\n40: - Custom resource definition modifications\n41: - User notification systems for impending cleanup\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Impact Analysis\n46: \n47: ### Dependencies\n48: \n49: | Package | Purpose |\n50: |---------|---------|\n51: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Kubernetes client interface |\n52: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Metadata and deletion options |\n53: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch` | Watch interface for resource monitoring |\n54: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n56: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n57: | `prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | Metrics exposition |\n58: | `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | Concurrent cleanup operations |\n59: \n60: ### Affected Components\n61: \n62: 1. **Workload Manager**: Receives deletion events for cleaned resources; must handle graceful termination\n63: 2. **Reconciler**: Processes status updates from cleanup operations; updates finalizers\n64: 3. **Metrics System**: Exposes cleanup metrics for monitoring dashboards\n65: 4. **Router Session Manager**: May need to invalidate sessions for cleaned resources\n66: \n67: ### Backward Compatibility\n68: \n69: - This is a new controller within agentd\n70: - No breaking changes to existing APIs\n71: - Configuration via environment variables with sensible defaults\n72: - Can be disabled via configuration flag\n73: \n74: ### Risk Assessment\n75: \n76: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n77: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n78: | Premature cleanup of active resources | Low | High | Conservative idle detection, last-activity tracking from workload manager |\n79: | Cleanup storm under load | Medium | Medium | Rate limiting, concurrent cleanup limits |\n80: | Resource leak if cleanup fails | Medium | Medium | Retry logic, metrics for failed cleanups |\n81: | Watch connection failures | Medium | Low | Exponential backoff, periodic full scans |\n82: | Namespace isolation violations | Low | High | Namespace-scoped clients, validation |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Alternatives Considered\n87: \n88: ### Alternative 1: TTL-Based Kubernetes Finalizers\n89: \n90: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes native TTL secondsAfterFinished on resources\n91: \n92: **Pros**:\n93: - Leverages Kubernetes garbage collection\n94: - No additional controller logic needed\n95: - Native integration with Kubernetes lifecycle\n96: \n97: **Cons**:\n98: - Requires CRD modifications\n99: - Only triggers after completion, not for idle resources\n100: - Less flexible timeout configuration\n101: \n102: **Decision**: Implement custom idle detection for more granular control.\n103: \n104: ### Alternative 2: Workload Manager Integrated Cleanup\n105: \n106: **Approach**: Add cleanup logic directly to workload manager reconciliation loop\n107: \n108: **Pros**:\n109: - Single reconciliation loop\n110: - Direct access to workload state\n111: - No inter-controller coordination\n112: \n113: **Cons**:\n114: - Bloated reconciliation logic\n115: - Cleanup delays during high reconciliation load\n116: - Harder to tune cleanup independently\n117: \n118: **Decision**: Separate controller for cleaner separation of concerns and independent tuning.\n119: \n120: ### Alternative 3: CronJob-Based Cleanup\n121: \n122: **Approach**: Deploy cleanup logic as periodic Kubernetes CronJob\n123: \n124: **Pros**:\n125: - Simple to understand and deploy\n126: - Kubernetes-native scheduling\n127: - No long-running process\n128: \n129: **Cons**:\n130: - No real-time idle detection\n131: - Potential race conditions with concurrent runs\n132: - Less responsive to load changes\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Continuous controller for better responsiveness and state tracking.\n135: \n136: ### Alternative 4: Label-Based Selection\n137: \n138: **Approach**: Use label selectors to mark resources for cleanup, separate finalizer processes them\n139: \n140: **Pros**:\n141: - Clear separation of detection and execution\n142: - Audit trail via labels\n143: - Easier debugging\n144: \n145: **Cons**:\n146: - Additional API surface (label management)\n147: - More complex state machine\n148: - Label cleanup required\n149: \n150: **Decision**: Direct deletion for simpler implementation; can add labels later for audit.\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Implementation Details\n155: \n156: ### IdleCleanupController Interface\n157: \n158: ```go\n159: type IdleCleanupController interface {\n160:     // Start starts the idle cleanup controller\n161:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n162:     \n163:     // Stop stops the controller gracefully\n164:     Stop()\n165:     \n166:     // CleanupNow triggers an immediate cleanup cycle\n167:     CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)\n168: }\n169: \n170: type CleanupResult struct {\n171:     AgentRuntimesCleaned   int\n172:     CodeInterpretersCleaned int\n173:     Errors                 []CleanupError\n174: }\n175: \n176: type CleanupError struct {\n177:     ResourceKind string\n178:     Name         string\n179:     Namespace    string\n180:     Error        error\n181: }\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### IdleTracker Interface\n185: \n186: ```go\n187: type IdleTracker interface {\n188:     // UpdateLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a resource\n189:     UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)\n190:     \n191:     // GetLastActivity retrieves the last activity timestamp\n192:     GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)\n193:     \n194:     // IsIdle checks if a resource is idle based on current time\n195:     IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool\n196:     \n197:     // Remove removes a resource from tracking\n198:     Remove(kind, namespace, name string)\n199:     \n200:     // ListIdleResources returns all idle resources exceeding timeout\n201:     ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey\n202: }\n203: \n204: type ResourceKey struct {\n205:     Kind      string\n206:     Namespace string\n207:     Name      string\n208: }\n209: ```\n210: \n211: ### Configuration\n212: \n213: ```go\n214: type CleanupConfig struct {\n215:     // AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout is the idle timeout for AgentRuntimes\n216:     AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration\n217:     \n218:     // CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout is the idle timeout for CodeInterpreters\n219:     CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration\n220:     \n221:     // CleanupInterval is how often to run cleanup cycles\n222:     CleanupInterval time.Duration\n223:     \n224:     // MaxConcurrentCleanups limits concurrent deletion operations\n225:     MaxConcurrentCleanups int\n226:     \n227:     // Enabled enables the idle cleanup controller\n228:     Enabled bool\n229:     \n230:     // DryRun enables dry-run mode (log only, no deletions)\n231:     DryRun bool\n232:     \n233:     // NamespaceAllowList restricts cleanup to specific namespaces (empty = all)\n234:     NamespaceAllowList []string\n235:     \n236:     // NamespaceDenyList excludes specific namespaces from cleanup\n237:     NamespaceDenyList []string\n238: }\n239: \n240: func DefaultCleanupConfig() *CleanupConfig {\n241:     return &CleanupConfig{\n242:         AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout:    30 * time.Minute,\n243:         CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n244:         CleanupInterval:           5 * time.Minute,\n245:         MaxConcurrentCleanups:     10,\n246:         Enabled:                   true,\n247:         DryRun:                    false,\n248:     }\n249: }\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### Metrics\n253: \n254: ```go\n255: type CleanupMetrics struct {\n256:     // agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal counts total AgentRuntime cleanups\n257:     agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter\n258:     \n259:     // codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal counts total CodeInterpreter cleanups\n260:     codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter\n261:     \n262:     // cleanupErrorsTotal counts cleanup errors by kind\n263:     cleanupErrorsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec\n264:     \n265:     // cleanupDurationSeconds tracks cleanup operation duration\n266:     cleanupDurationSeconds *prometheus.HistogramVec\n267:     \n268:     // idleResourcesDetected tracks detected idle resources\n269:     idleResourcesDetected *prometheus.GaugeVec\n270: }\n271: \n272: func (m *CleanupMetrics) RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)\n273: func (m *CleanupMetrics) SetIdleCount(kind string, count int)\n274: func (m *CleanupMetrics) RecordError(kind string)\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ### Idle Detection Logic\n278: \n279: ```go\n280: type idleTracker struct {\n281:     mu           sync.RWMutex\n282:     lastActivity map[ResourceKey]time.Time\n283:     logger       klog.Logger\n284: }\n285: \n286: func (t *idleTracker) UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time) {\n287:     t.mu.Lock()\n288:     defer t.mu.Unlock()\n289:     \n290:     key := ResourceKey{Kind: kind, Namespace: namespace, Name: name}\n291:     t.lastActivity[key] = timestamp\n292:     \n293:     t.logger.V(4).Info(\"Updated last activity\",\n294:         \"kind\", kind,\n295:         \"namespace\", namespace,\n296:         \"name\", name,\n297:         \"timestamp\", timestamp)\n298: }\n299: \n300: func (t *idleTracker) IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool {\n301:     t.mu.RLock()\n302:     defer t.mu.RUnlock()\n303:     \n304:     key := ResourceKey{Kind: kind, Namespace: namespace, Name: name}\n305:     lastActivity, exists := t.lastActivity[key]\n306:     \n307:     if !exists {\n308:         // No activity recorded; use creation time as fallback\n309:         return true\n310:     }\n311:     \n312:     return time.Since(lastActivity) >= timeout\n313: }\n314: \n315: func (t *idleTracker) ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey {\n316:     t.mu.RLock()\n317:     defer t.mu.RUnlock()\n318:     \n319:     now := time.Now()\n320:     var idle []ResourceKey\n321:     \n322:     for key, lastActivity := range t.lastActivity {\n323:         if now.Sub(lastActivity) >= timeout {\n324:             idle = append(idle, key)\n325:         }\n326:     }\n327:     \n328:     return idle\n329: }\n330: ```\n331: \n332: ### Cleanup Controller Implementation\n333: \n334: ```go\n335: type idleCleanupController struct {\n336:     config       *CleanupConfig\n337:     agentClient  versioned.Interface\n338:     idleTracker  IdleTracker\n339:     metrics      *CleanupMetrics\n340:     logger       klog.Logger\n341:     stopCh       chan struct{}\n342:     wg           sync.WaitGroup\n343: }\n344: \n345: func (c *idleCleanupController) Start(ctx context.Context) error {\n346:     if !c.config.Enabled {\n347:         c.logger.Info(\"Idle cleanup controller is disabled\")\n348:         return nil\n349:     }\n350:     \n351:     c.logger.Info(\"Starting idle cleanup controller\",\n352:         \"agentRuntimeTimeout\", c.config.AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout,\n353:         \"codeInterpreterTimeout\", c.config.CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout,\n354:         \"cleanupInterval\", c.config.CleanupInterval)\n355:     \n356:     // Start watch for resource status updates\n357:     c.wg.Add(1)\n358:     go func() {\n359:         defer c.wg.Done()\n360:         c.watchResources(ctx)\n361:     }()\n362:     \n363:     // Start periodic cleanup\n364:     c.wg.Add(1)\n365:     go func() {\n366:         defer c.wg.Done()\n367:         ticker := time.NewTicker(c.config.CleanupInterval)\n368:         defer ticker.Stop()\n369:         \n370:         for {\n371:             select {\n372:             case <-ctx.Done():\n373:                 return\n374:             case <-c.stopCh:\n375:                 return\n376:             case <-ticker.C:\n377:                 c.runCleanup(ctx)\n378:             }\n379:         }\n380:     }()\n381:     \n382:     return nil\n383: }\n384: \n385: func (c *idleCleanupController) runCleanup(ctx context.Context) {\n386:     c.logger.V(4).Info(\"Starting cleanup cycle\")\n387:     \n388:     var g errgroup.Group\n389:     g.SetLimit(c.config.MaxConcurrentCleanups)\n390:     \n391:     // Clean idle AgentRuntimes\n392:     agentIdle := c.idleTracker.ListIdleResources(c.config.AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout)\n393:     c.metrics.SetIdleCount(\"AgentRuntime\", len(agentIdle))\n394:     \n395:     for _, key := range agentIdle {\n396:         if !c.isNamespaceAllowed(key.Namespace) {\n397:             continue\n398:         }\n399:         \n400:         g.Go(func() error {\n401:             return c.cleanupResource(ctx, key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n402:         })\n403:     }\n404:     \n405:     // Clean idle CodeInterpreters\n406:     ciIdle := c.idleTracker.ListIdleResources(c.config.CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout)\n407:     c.metrics.SetIdleCount(\"CodeInterpreter\", len(ciIdle))\n408:     \n409:     for _, key := range ciIdle {\n410:         if !c.isNamespaceAllowed(key.Namespace) {\n411:             continue\n412:         }\n413:         \n414:         g.Go(func() error {\n415:             return c.cleanupResource(ctx, key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n416:         })\n417:     }\n418:     \n419:     if err := g.Wait(); err != nil {\n420:         c.logger.Error(err, \"Cleanup cycle completed with errors\")\n421:     } else {\n422:         c.logger.V(4).Info(\"Cleanup cycle completed successfully\")\n423:     }\n424: }\n425: \n426: func (c *idleCleanupController) cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error {\n427:     start := time.Now()\n428:     var err error\n429:     \n430:     if c.config.DryRun {\n431:         c.logger.Info(\"[DRY RUN] Would clean idle resource\",\n432:             \"kind\", kind,\n433:             \"namespace\", namespace,\n434:             \"name\", name)\n435:         c.metrics.RecordCleanup(kind, time.Since(start), nil)\n436:         return nil\n437:     }\n438:     \n439:     switch kind {\n440:     case \"AgentRuntime\":\n441:         err = c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(\n442:             ctx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n443:                 GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To(int64(30)),\n444:                 PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationForeground),\n445:             })\n446:     case \"CodeInterpreter\":\n447:         err = c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete(\n448:             ctx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n449:                 GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To(int64(30)),\n450:                 PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationForeground),\n451:             })\n452:     default:\n453:         err = fmt.Errorf(\"unknown resource kind: %s\", kind)\n454:     }\n455:     \n456:     c.metrics.RecordCleanup(kind, time.Since(start), err)\n457:     \n458:     if err != nil {\n459:         c.logger.Error(err, \"Failed to cleanup idle resource\",\n460:             \"kind\", kind,\n461:             \"namespace\", namespace,\n462:             \"name\", name)\n463:         return err\n464:     }\n465:     \n466:     c.logger.Info(\"Cleaned up idle resource\",\n467:         \"kind\", kind,\n468:         \"namespace\", namespace,\n469:         \"name\", name)\n470:     \n471:     // Remove from idle tracker\n472:     c.idleTracker.Remove(kind, namespace, name)\n473:     \n474:     return nil\n475: }\n476: \n477: func (c *idleCleanupController) watchResources(ctx context.Context) {\n478:     // Watch AgentRuntimes\n479:     go c.watchAgentRuntimes(ctx)\n480:     \n481:     // Watch CodeInterpreters\n482:     go c.watchCodeInterpreters(ctx)\n483:     \n484:     <-ctx.Done()\n485: }\n486: \n487: func (c *idleCleanupController) watchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context) {\n488:     watcher, err := c.agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(metav1.NamespaceAll).Watch(\n489:         ctx, metav1.ListOptions{\n490:             TimeoutSeconds: ptr.To(int64(300)),\n491:         })\n492:     if err != nil {\n493:         c.logger.Error(err, \"Failed to watch AgentRuntimes\")\n494:         return\n495:     }\n496:     \n497:     for {\n498:         select {\n499:         case <-ctx.Done():\n500:             watcher.Stop()\n501:             return\n502:         case event, ok := <-watcher.ResultChan():\n503:             if !ok {\n504:                 return\n505:             }\n506:             \n507:             ar, ok := event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n508:             if !ok {\n509:                 continue\n510:             }\n511:             \n512:             key := ResourceKey{\n513:                 Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n514:                 Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n515:                 Name:      ar.Name,\n516:             }\n517:             \n518:             switch event.Type {\n519:             case watch.Added, watch.Modified:\n520:                 // Update last activity from status.lastActivity or metadata.creationTimestamp\n521:                 c.updateResourceActivity(key, ar.Status.LastActivityTime, ar.CreationTimestamp)\n522:             case watch.Deleted:\n523:                 c.idleTracker.Remove(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name)\n524:             }\n525:         }\n526:     }\n527: }\n528: \n529: func (c *idleCleanupController) watchCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context) {\n530:     // Similar to watchAgentRuntimes but for CodeInterpreters\n531:     // ... implementation ...\n532: }\n533: \n534: func (c *idleCleanupController) updateResourceActivity(key ResourceKey, lastActivity, creation metav1.Time) {\n535:     if !lastActivity.IsZero() {\n536:         c.idleTracker.UpdateLastActivity(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name, lastActivity.Time)\n537:     } else {\n538:         c.idleTracker.UpdateLastActivity(key.Kind, key.Namespace, key.Name, creation.Time)\n539:     }\n540: }\n541: \n542: func (c *idleCleanupController) isNamespaceAllowed(namespace string) bool {\n543:     // Check deny list first\n544:     for _, denied := range c.config.NamespaceDenyList {\n545:         if namespace == denied {\n546:             return false\n547:         }\n548:     }\n549:     \n550:     // Check allow list\n551:     if len(c.config.NamespaceAllowList) == 0 {\n552:         return true\n553:     }\n554:     \n555:     for _, allowed := range c.config.NamespaceAllowList {\n556:         if namespace == allowed {\n557:             return true\n558:         }\n559:     }\n560:     \n561:     return false\n562: }\n563: ```\n564: \n565: ---\n566: \n567: ## Configuration Reference\n568: \n569: ### Environment Variables\n570: \n571: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n572: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n573: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED` | No | `true` | Enable/disable idle cleanup |\n574: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN` | No | `false` | Log only, no deletions |\n575: | `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | No | `30m` | AgentRuntime idle timeout |\n576: | `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | No | `15m` | CodeInterpreter idle timeout |\n577: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL` | No | `5m` | Cleanup cycle interval |\n578: | `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS` | No | `10` | Max concurrent deletions |\n579: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST` | No | `` | Comma-separated allowed namespaces |\n580: | `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST` | No | `kube-system,kube-public` | Comma-separated excluded namespaces |\n581: \n582: ### Example Configuration\n583: \n584: ```go\n585: config := &CleanupConfig{\n586:     AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout:    30 * time.Minute,\n587:     CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n588:     CleanupInterval:           5 * time.Minute,\n589:     MaxConcurrentCleanups:     10,\n590:     Enabled:                   true,\n591:     DryRun:                    false,\n592:     NamespaceAllowList:        []string{\"default\", \"agent-workloads\"},\n593:     NamespaceDenyList:         []string{\"kube-system\", \"kube-public\", \"monitoring\"},\n594: }\n595: ```\n596: \n597: ---\n598: \n599: ## Testing Strategy\n600: \n601: ### Unit Tests\n602: \n603: | Test | Purpose |\n604: |------|---------|\n605: | `TestIdleTracker_UpdateLastActivity` | Verify activity timestamp updates |\n606: | `TestIdleTracker_IsIdle` | Test idle detection logic |\n607: | `TestIdleTracker_ListIdleResources` | Test listing idle resources |\n608: | `TestIdleTracker_Remove` | Test resource removal from tracking |\n609: | `TestCleanupController_runCleanup` | Test cleanup cycle logic |\n610: | `TestCleanupController_cleanupResource` | Test single resource cleanup |\n611: | `TestCleanupController_isNamespaceAllowed` | Test namespace filtering |\n612: | `TestCleanupController_DryRun` | Verify dry-run mode |\n613: | `TestCleanupMetrics_RecordCleanup` | Test metrics recording |\n614: \n615: ### Integration Tests\n616: \n617: | Test | Purpose |\n618: |------|---------|\n619: | `TestIntegration_AgentRuntimeCleanup` | Full AgentRuntime cleanup flow |\n620: | `TestIntegration_CodeInterpreterCleanup` | Full CodeInterpreter cleanup flow |\n621: | `TestIntegration_ConcurrentCleanups` | Verify concurrent cleanup limits |\n622: | `TestIntegration_WatchReconnect` | Test watch reconnection on failure |\n623: | `TestIntegration_MetricsExposition` | Verify metrics are exposed correctly |\n624: \n625: ### Test Fixtures\n626: \n627: ```go\n628: func newFakeIdleCleanupController(t *testing.T) (*idleCleanupController, *fake.Clientset) {\n629:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n630:     config := DefaultCleanupConfig()\n631:     config.Enabled = true\n632:     config.DryRun = false\n633:     \n634:     tracker := &idleTracker{\n635:         lastActivity: make(map[ResourceKey]time.Time),\n636:         logger:       klog.Background(),\n637:     }\n638:     \n639:     metrics := NewCleanupMetrics(prometheus.NewRegistry())\n640:     \n641:     controller := &idleCleanupController{\n642:         config:       config,\n643:         agentClient:  fakeClient,\n644:         idleTracker:  tracker,\n645:         metrics:      metrics,\n646:         logger:       klog.Background(),\n647:         stopCh:       make(chan struct{}),\n648:     }\n649:     \n650:     return controller, fakeClient\n651: }\n652: \n653: func createTestAgentRuntime(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n654:     return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n655:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n656:             Name:      name,\n657:             Namespace: namespace,\n658:         },\n659:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n660:             Phase: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning,\n661:         },\n662:     }\n663: }\n664: ```\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## Acceptance Criteria\n669: \n670: - [ ] `IdleCleanupController` interface implements all required methods\n671: - [ ] `IdleTracker` correctly tracks last activity timestamps\n672: - [ ] Idle detection works with configurable timeouts per resource type\n673: - [ ] Namespace allow/deny lists are respected\n674: - [ ] Dry-run mode logs without deleting\n675: - [ ] Concurrent cleanup limits are enforced\n676: - [ ] Metrics are exposed for monitoring\n677: - [ ] Watch reconnection handles connection failures\n678: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n679: - [ ] Integration tests pass with fake clients\n680: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n681: - [ ] Documentation includes configuration examples\n682: - [ ] Graceful shutdown on controller stop\n683: \n684: ---\n685: \n686: ## Error Handling\n687: \n688: ### CleanupError Types\n689: \n690: ```go\n691: type CleanupErrorType string\n692: \n693: const (\n694:     CleanupErrorNotFound      CleanupErrorType = \"not_found\"\n695:     CleanupErrorPermission    CleanupErrorType = \"permission_denied\"\n696:     CleanupErrorTimeout       CleanupErrorType = \"timeout\"\n697:     CleanupErrorConflict      CleanupErrorType = \"conflict\"\n698:     CleanupErrorUnknown       CleanupErrorType = \"unknown\"\n699: )\n700: \n701: type CleanupError struct {\n702:     Type       CleanupErrorType\n703:     ResourceKind string\n704:     Namespace  string\n705:     Name       string\n706:     Message    string\n707:     Underlying error\n708: }\n709: \n710: func (e *CleanupError) Error() string {\n711:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup error [%s] for %s/%s/%s: %s\",\n712:         e.Type, e.ResourceKind, e.Namespace, e.Name, e.Message)\n713: }\n714: ```\n715: \n716: ### Error Conditions\n717: \n718: | Condition | Error Type | Handling | Description |\n719: |-----------|------------|----------|-------------|\n720: | Resource already deleted | `CleanupErrorNotFound` | Ignore | Resource was cleaned by another process |\n721: | Permission denied | `CleanupErrorPermission` | Log & retry | Insufficient RBAC permissions |\n722: | Deletion timeout | `CleanupErrorTimeout` | Log & retry | Resource deletion did not complete |\n723: | Finalizer conflict | `CleanupErrorConflict` | Log & skip | Resource has blocking finalizers |\n724: | Unknown API error | `CleanupErrorUnknown` | Log & retry | Uncategorized error |\n725: \n726: ---\n727: \n728: ## Future Considerations\n729: \n730: 1. **Activity Webhooks**: Receive activity notifications from workload manager for precise idle detection\n731: 2. **Graduated Timeouts**: Increase idle timeout for resources that are frequently recreated\n732: 3. **Pre-Cleanup Notification**: Emit events before cleanup for user awareness\n733: 4. **Resource-Specific Policies**: Allow per-resource idle timeout overrides via annotations\n734: 5. **Cluster-Aware Scheduling**: Reduce cleanup frequency during high cluster load\n735: 6. **Audit Logging**: Log all cleanup operations to audit trail\n736: 7. **Custom Resource Conditions**: Add `IdleCleanupCandidate` condition to resources\n737: \n738: ---\n739: \n740: ## References\n741: \n742: - AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n743: - AR-016: PicoD File Management API\n744: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go Documentation\n745: - `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/`: Workload Manager Reconciler\n746: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`: AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Types\n747: - Kubernetes Garbage Collection: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/garbage-collection/\n\n(End of file - total 747 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (AR-018)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement an idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller provides:\n\n1. **Resource Reclamation**: Automatically clean up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters to free cluster resources\n2. **Configurable Idle Detection**: Support per-resource-type idle timeout configuration\n3. **Graceful Termination**: Properly finalize resources before deletion with status updates\n4. **Observability**: Emit metrics and logs for cleanup operations\n5. **Safe Operation**: Respect resource11s and avoid cleaning resources with active workloads\n\nThis implementation builds upon the client-go infrastructure from `deployment/client-go.md` and integrates with the workload manager's reconciliation loop to ensure cleaned resources are properly handled.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775862881072,"end":1775862881115}}}}
