{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862980473,"sessionID":"ses_28653205affeCYrhnPGU1oCRmh","part":{"id":"prt_d79ad3e69001nLY5OsaOUNx5wL","messageID":"msg_d79ad3572001ajD1JrzcU9HP60","sessionID":"ses_28653205affeCYrhnPGU1oCRmh","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_58343438d29a4fd18ae83da7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","content":"# AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/agentd` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Configuration Structure (`config.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n  - Define package `agentd` with required imports\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `CleanupConfig` struct in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n  - Fields: `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CleanupInterval time.Duration`, `MaxConcurrentCleanups int`, `Enabled bool`, `DryRun bool`, `NamespaceAllowList []string`, `NamespaceDenyList []string`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Implement `DefaultCleanupConfig() *CleanupConfig` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n  - Return config with: AgentRuntime timeout 30m, CodeInterpreter timeout 15m, interval 5m, max concurrent 10, enabled true, dry run false\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `LoadCleanupConfigFromEnv() (*CleanupConfig, error)` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n  - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED` (default: true)\n  - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN` (default: false)\n  - Load `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT` (default: 30m)\n  - Load `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT` (default: 15m)\n  - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL` (default: 5m)\n  - Load `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS` (default: 10)\n  - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST` (comma-separated, default: empty)\n  - Load `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST` (default: kube-system,kube-public)\n  - Parse duration strings, log warnings and use defaults on parse failures\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `Validate(c *CleanupConfig) error` in `pkg/agentd/config.go`\n  - Validate timeouts are positive\n  - Validate CleanupInterval is positive\n  - Validate MaxConcurrentCleanups > 0\n  - Validate NamespaceDenyList includes system namespaces\n\n### Phase 2: CleanupError Types (`errors.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `CleanupErrorType` type and constants in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n  - Type: `CleanupErrorType` (string alias)\n  - Constants: `CleanupErrorNotFound`, `CleanupErrorPermission`, `CleanupErrorTimeout`, `CleanupErrorConflict`, `CleanupErrorUnknown`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `CleanupError` struct in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n  - Fields: `Type CleanupErrorType`, `ResourceKind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`, `Message string`, `Underlying error`\n  - Method: `Error() string` with format \"cleanup error [%s] for %s/%s/%s: %s\"\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `NewCleanupError(errType CleanupErrorType, kind, namespace, name, message string, underlying error) *CleanupError` in `pkg/agentd/errors.go`\n\n### Phase 3: IdleTracker Interface and Implementation (`idle_tracker.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Define `ResourceKey` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - Fields: `Kind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Define `IdleTracker` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - Methods: `UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)`, `GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)`, `IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool`, `Remove(kind, namespace, name string)`, `ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Define `idleTracker` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - Fields: `mu sync.RWMutex`, `lastActivity map[ResourceKey]time.Time`, `logger klog.Logger`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `NewIdleTracker(logger klog.Logger) IdleTracker` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - Initialize lastActivity map\n  - Return initialized tracker\n\n- [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `UpdateLastActivity` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - Lock mutex, update map, log at V(4)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `GetLastActivity` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - RLock mutex, return timestamp and exists bool\n\n- [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `IsIdle` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - Return true if no activity recorded\n  - Return true if time.Since(lastActivity) >= timeout\n  - Return false otherwise\n\n- [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `Remove` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - Lock mutex, delete from map\n\n- [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `ListIdleResources` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go`\n  - RLock mutex, iterate map, collect idle resources\n\n### Phase 4: CleanupMetrics (`cleanup_metrics.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Define `CleanupMetrics` struct in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n  - Fields: `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter`, `codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal prometheus.Counter`, `cleanupErrorsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec`, `cleanupDurationSeconds *prometheus.HistogramVec`, `idleResourcesDetected *prometheus.GaugeVec`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewCleanupMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) *CleanupMetrics` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n  - Initialize all metrics with proper labels\n  - Register metrics with provided registerer\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)` method in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n  - Increment appropriate counter based on kind\n  - Record duration in histogram\n  - Increment error counter if err != nil\n\n- [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `SetIdleCount(kind string, count int)` method in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n  - Set gauge for idle resource count\n\n- [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `RecordError(kind string)` method in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go`\n  - Increment error counter with kind label\n\n### Phase 5: IdleCleanupController Implementation (`idle_cleanup.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Define `CleanupResult` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Fields: `AgentRuntimesCleaned int`, `CodeInterpretersCleaned int`, `Errors []CleanupError`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Define `IdleCleanupController` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Methods: `Start(ctx context.Context) error`, `Stop()`, `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Define `idleCleanupController` struct in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Fields: `config *CleanupConfig`, `agentClient versioned.Interface`, `idleTracker IdleTracker`, `metrics *CleanupMetrics`, `logger klog.Logger`, `stopCh chan struct{}`, `wg sync.WaitGroup`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `NewIdleCleanupController(config *CleanupConfig, agentClient versioned.Interface, idleTracker IdleTracker, metrics *CleanupMetrics, logger klog.Logger) IdleCleanupController` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `Start(ctx context.Context) error` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Check if enabled, return early if disabled\n  - Start watch goroutine for resources\n  - Start periodic cleanup goroutine with ticker\n  - Log startup message with configuration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `Stop()` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Close stopCh\n  - Wait for goroutines to complete via wg.Wait()\n  - Log shutdown completion\n\n- [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Run immediate cleanup cycle\n  - Return CleanupResult with counts and errors\n\n- [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement `runCleanup(ctx context.Context)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Create errgroup with MaxConcurrentCleanups limit\n  - List idle AgentRuntimes and submit cleanup tasks\n  - List idle CodeInterpreters and submit cleanup tasks\n  - Wait for all tasks and log completion status\n\n- [ ] **TASK-048**: Implement `cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Handle DryRun mode (log only)\n  - Delete AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter based on kind\n  - Use GracePeriodSeconds: 30, PropagationPolicy: Foreground\n  - Record metrics\n  - Remove from idle tracker on success\n  - Handle NotFound errors gracefully\n\n- [ ] **TASK-049**: Implement `isNamespaceAllowed(namespace string) bool` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Check deny list first (returns false if matched)\n  - Check allow list (returns true if empty or matched)\n\n### Phase 6: Resource Watching (`idle_cleanup.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `watchResources(ctx context.Context)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Start watchAgentRuntimes goroutine\n  - Start watchCodeInterpreters goroutine\n  - Wait for context cancellation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `watchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Create watch with 300s timeout\n  - Handle Added/Modified events: update idle tracker with LastActivityTime or CreationTimestamp\n  - Handle Deleted events: remove from tracker\n  - Implement reconnection with exponential backoff on failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement `watchCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Similar to watchAgentRuntimes but for CodeInterpreter resources\n\n- [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `updateResourceActivity(key ResourceKey, lastActivity, creation metav1.Time)` method in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Use LastActivityTime if not zero\n  - Fall back to CreationTimestamp otherwise\n\n### Phase 7: Unit Tests\n\n#### Config Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestDefaultCleanupConfig` in `pkg/agentd/config_test.go`\n  - Verify default timeouts (30m, 15m)\n  - Verify default interval (5m)\n  - Verify MaxConcurrentCleanups (10)\n  - Verify Enabled is true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestLoadCleanupConfigFromEnv_Success` in `pkg/agentd/config_test.go`\n  - Set environment variables\n  - Verify config loaded correctly\n  - Clean up environment after test\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestLoadCleanupConfigFromEnv_InvalidDuration` in `pkg/agentd/config_test.go`\n  - Set invalid duration string\n  - Verify warning logged and default used\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestCleanupConfig_Validate` in `pkg/agentd/config_test.go`\n  - Test negative timeout returns error\n  - Test zero MaxConcurrentCleanups returns error\n  - Test valid config returns nil\n\n#### Error Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestCleanupError_Error` in `pkg/agentd/errors_test.go`\n  - Verify Error() string format includes all fields\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestNewCleanupError` in `pkg/agentd/errors_test.go`\n  - Verify all fields set correctly\n\n#### IdleTracker Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `TestIdleTracker_UpdateLastActivity` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go`\n  - Update activity timestamp\n  - Verify retrievable via GetLastActivity\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `TestIdleTracker_IsIdle_True` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go`\n  - Resource idle longer than timeout\n  - Verify IsIdle returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-022**: Create `TestIdleTracker_IsIdle_False` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go`\n  - Resource active within timeout\n  - Verify IsIdle returns false\n\n- [ ] **TEST-023**: Create `TestIdleTracker_IsIdle_NoActivity` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go`\n  - Resource never had activity recorded\n  - Verify IsIdle returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-024**: Create `TestIdleTracker_ListIdleResources` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go`\n  - Mix of idle and active resources\n  - Verify only idle resources returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-025**: Create `TestIdleTracker_Remove` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go`\n  - Remove resource from tracker\n  - Verify no longer appears in ListIdleResources\n\n- [ ] **TEST-026**: Create `TestIdleTracker_ThreadSafety` in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go`\n  - Concurrent UpdateLastActivity calls\n  - Verify no data races (run with -race)\n\n#### Metrics Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `TestCleanupMetrics_RecordCleanup_Success` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics_test.go`\n  - Record successful cleanup\n  - Verify counter incremented and duration recorded\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: Create `TestCleanupMetrics_RecordCleanup_Error` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics_test.go`\n  - Record failed cleanup\n  - Verify error counter incremented\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: Create `TestCleanupMetrics_SetIdleCount` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics_test.go`\n  - Set idle count\n  - Verify gauge updated\n\n#### Controller Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `TestIdleCleanupController_Start_Disabled` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Config.Enabled = false\n  - Verify Start returns without starting watches\n\n- [ ] **TEST-041**: Create `TestIdleCleanupController_Stop` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Start controller, then Stop\n  - Verify graceful shutdown completes\n\n- [ ] **TEST-042**: Create `TestIdleCleanupController_runCleanup` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Setup idle resources\n  - Run cleanup cycle\n  - Verify resources deleted\n\n- [ ] **TEST-043**: Create `TestIdleCleanupController_cleanupResource_DryRun` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Config.DryRun = true\n  - Verify resource not deleted, only logged\n\n- [ ] **TEST-044**: Create `TestIdleCleanupController_cleanupResource_NotFound` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Resource already deleted\n  - Verify NotFound error handled gracefully\n\n- [ ] **TEST-045**: Create `TestIdleCleanupController_isNamespaceAllowed` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Test allow list filtering\n  - Test deny list filtering\n  - Test deny list takes precedence\n\n- [ ] **TEST-046**: Create `TestIdleCleanupController_CleanupNow` in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n  - Trigger immediate cleanup\n  - Verify CleanupResult returned with counts\n\n### Phase 8: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `TestIntegration_AgentRuntimeCleanup` in `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go`\n  - Use fake clientset\n  - Create test AgentRuntime with old LastActivityTime\n  - Run cleanup\n  - Verify resource deleted\n\n- [ ] **TEST-051**: Create `TestIntegration_CodeInterpreterCleanup` in `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go`\n  - Use fake clientset\n  - Create test CodeInterpreter with old LastActivityTime\n  - Run cleanup\n  - Verify resource deleted\n\n- [ ] **TEST-052**: Create `TestIntegration_ConcurrentCleanups` in `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go`\n  - Create many idle resources\n  - Verify MaxConcurrentCleanups respected\n\n- [ ] **TEST-053**: Create `TestIntegration_WatchReconnect` in `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go`\n  - Simulate watch failure\n  - Verify reconnection with backoff\n\n- [ ] **TEST-054**: Create `TestIntegration_MetricsExposition` in `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go`\n  - Run cleanup operations\n  - Verify metrics exposed via Prometheus registry\n\n### Phase 9: Test Utilities\n\n- [ ] **TEST-060**: Create `newFakeIdleCleanupController(t *testing.T) (*idleCleanupController, *fake.Clientset)` helper in `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go`\n  - Setup fake clientset\n  - Initialize controller with test config\n\n- [ ] **TEST-061**: Create `createTestAgentRuntime(namespace, name string, lastActivity time.Time) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` helper in `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-062**: Create `createTestCodeInterpreter(namespace, name string, lastActivity time.Time) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` helper in `pkg/agentd/integration_test.go`\n\n### Phase 10: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types in `config.go`, `errors.go`, `idle_tracker.go`, `cleanup_metrics.go`, `idle_cleanup.go`\n  - Include parameter descriptions\n  - Include return value descriptions\n  - Include error conditions\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add usage examples in doc comments\n  - Example: creating IdleCleanupController\n  - Example: configuring idle timeouts\n  - Example: integrating with agentd\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Update `pkg/agentd/README.md`\n  - Document idle cleanup controller\n  - Include configuration options and environment variables\n  - Include metrics documentation\n  - Include operational guide\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Add security and operations documentation\n  - Namespace isolation considerations\n  - RBAC requirements\n  - Monitoring and alerting recommendations\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `IdleCleanupController` interface implements all required methods\n- [ ] `IdleTracker` correctly tracks last activity timestamps\n- [ ] Idle detection works with configurable timeouts per resource type\n- [ ] Namespace allow/deny lists are respected\n- [ ] Dry-run mode logs without deleting\n- [ ] Concurrent cleanup limits are enforced\n- [ ] Metrics are exposed for monitoring\n- [ ] Watch reconnection handles connection failures\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with fake clients\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Documentation includes configuration examples\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown on controller stop\n- [ ] All files have corresponding test files\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Kubernetes client interfaces |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated | Typed client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Generated | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch` | External | Watch event streaming |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | External | Metadata, deletion options |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n| `prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | External | Metrics exposition |\n| `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | External | Concurrent cleanup with limits |\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001 → TASK-005 (Configuration)\n    ↓\nTASK-010 → TASK-012 (Error types)\n    ↓\nTASK-020 → TASK-028 (IdleTracker)\n    ↓\nTASK-030 → TASK-034 (CleanupMetrics)\n    ↓\nTASK-040 → TASK-049 (IdleCleanupController core)\n    ↓\nTASK-050 → TASK-053 (Resource watching)\n    ↓\nTEST-001 → TEST-046 (Unit tests)\n    ↓\nTEST-050 → TEST-062 (Integration tests)\n    ↓\nDOC-001 → DOC-004 (Documentation)\n```\n\n## Coverage Verification\n\n- [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n  - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/agentd/... ./pkg/agentd/...`\n  - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n  - Verify config.go, errors.go, idle_tracker.go, cleanup_metrics.go, idle_cleanup.go all covered\n  - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775862980460,"end":1775862980469}}}}
